                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 3691/301.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Chargé <persName type="from">Brown</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.—Extract.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">La Union, Salvador</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1907-04-04">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 4, 1907</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Mr. Brown reports that the President of Guatemala, through the President of
                    Salvador, sends him a special message expressing an earnest desire for the
                    successful mediation for peace in Central America, and that Salvador and
                    Nicaragua have avoided any declaration of war or formal admission of same, but a
                    peace conference is absolutely necessary to clear the situation.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
